# Ensure selected_predictors contains valid column names
selected_predictors <- c("latitude", "longitude", "depth", "mag", "magType.mb", "magType.mb_lg", "magType.md", "magType.ml", "magType.mwb", "magType.mwr", "nst", "gap", "dmin", "rms", "horizontalError", "depthError", "magError", "magNst")
X_train <- earthquake_d_norm[, selected_predictors]
y_train<-earthquake_d$mag
set.seed(123)  # For reproducibility
train_index <- createDataPartition(y_train, p = 0.8, list = FALSE)
X_train <- X_train[train_index, ]
y_train <- y_train[train_index]
X_test <- X_train[-train_index, ]
y_test <- y_train[-train_index]
preproc <- preProcess(X_train, method = c('center', 'scale'))
X_train_norm <- predict(preproc, X_train)
X_test_norm <- predict(preproc, X_test)
library(class)
knn_model <- knn(train = X_train_norm, test = X_test_norm, cl = y_train, k = 5)
predictions_knn <- knn_model
# Convert predictions and y_test to factors
predictions <- factor(predictions_knn)
y_test <- factor(y_test)
# Convert predictions and y_test to character vectors
predictions_char <- as.character(predictions)
y_test_char <- as.character(y_test)
# Match levels by converting to factors with the same levels
predictions_factor <- factor(predictions_char, levels = unique(c(predictions_char, y_test_char)))
y_test_factor <- factor(y_test_char, levels = unique(c(predictions_char, y_test_char)))
# Create the confusion matrix
conf_matrix <- confusionMatrix(predictions_factor, y_test_factor)
#print(conf_matrix)
#seperate all the metrices from the confusion matrix
Accuracy_knn<-conf_matrix$overall['Accuracy']
precision_knn <- conf_matrix$byClass['Precision']
recall_knn <- conf_matrix$byClass['Recall']
f1_score_knn <- conf_matrix$byClass['F1']
# training the naive bayes
library(e1071)
nb_model <- naiveBayes(X_train_norm, as.factor(y_train))
predictions_nb <- predict(nb_model, newdata = X_test_norm)
#convert the prediction to factor and making them to same level.
naive_pre <- as.factor(predictions_nb)
common_levels <- union(levels(naive_pre), levels(y_test_char))
naive_factor <- factor(naive_pre, levels = common_levels)
y_test_factor <- factor(y_test_char, levels = common_levels)
#confusion matrix
conf <- confusionMatrix(naive_factor, y_test_factor)
#print(conf)
Accuracy_nb<- conf$overall['Accuracy']
precision_nb <- conf$byClass['Precision']
recall_nb <- conf$byClass['Recall']
f1_score_nb <- conf$byClass['F1']
comparison_table <- data.frame(
  Model = c("KNN", "Naive Bayes"),
  Accuracy = c(Accuracy_knn, Accuracy_nb),
  Precision = c(precision_knn, precision_nb),
  Recall = c(recall_knn, recall_nb),
  F1_Score = c(f1_score_knn, f1_score_nb)
)
print(comparison_table)
